title: Really great
text:
Love these Jeans! I got the size Med, Iâ€™m 5'1" 128lbs. I normally wear a 28-30 waist, so they are just a little loose on my waist, but I hope they will tighten up and shrink in a hot wash and hot dryer. These are very hip-hop, cool-girl jeans. They are very loose fitting everywhere and are not a stretch denim. They are high-waisted. The jeans have cute metal rivets on the pockets and thank god there is no dumb logo on the pocket (or I would have sent em back). Jeans are a dark'ish navy blue and a nice med-weight denim, not stiff. Because I am short I will need to cut a lot off the bottom. Keep in mind if you do cut a lot off the bottom they may loose their barrel leg shape.
Measurements for the Med. I was sent:
Jeans Front inseam -13"
Jeans Back inseam -16"
Jeans waist -34"
Jeans length from top of waistband to bottom - 44"

title: Good jeans
text:
Got mine a size up on purpose for extra sag. Good yellow stitches, shaped just like the ad pic. Keep in mind these are inexpensive so the material is nothing special, quite thin.
Big pockets! Very roomy.
